{
  "batch": "Package Organization",
  "batch_index": 4,
  "assessments": {
    "high_level_elegance": 72.0
  },
  "dimension_notes": {
    "high_level_elegance": {
      "evidence": [
        "config package owns both mutable process globals and runtime event-listener behavior in one place (`goseg/config/bootstrap.go` initializes state, file paths, readiness, and starts `ConfChannel()`; `goseg/config/config_events.go` contains the blocking channel listener loop).",
        "The package exposes multiple package-level mutable globals (`BasePath`, `Architecture`, `DebugMode`, `DockerDir`, `Ready`, `isEMMCMachine`, etc.) instead of a single explicit ownership boundary.",
        "Container type handling in orchestration is split across multiple files by raw string dispatch (`ContainerConfigForTypeWithRuntime`) and repeated adapter construction in `container_bridge.go`, forcing each new container type to cross-cut files manually.",
        "Startram restore logic is split across `backup_restore_runtime.go` and `backup_service.go` using parallel default singletons (`defaultRestoreBackupRuntime` and `defaultBackupInfrastructureService`) rather than a single, clearly owned restore orchestration surface."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "medium"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "config_singleton_boundary",
      "summary": "Config package blurs process-global state ownership by combining mutable singleton config state with asynchronous event-listener orchestration.",
      "related_files": ["goseg/config/bootstrap.go", "goseg/config/config_events.go"],
      "evidence": [
        "`Initialize()` sets globals and then starts `go ConfChannel()`; `ConfChannel()` contains an unscoped infinite loop reading `system.ConfChannel` in the same package as config persistence/state.",
        "`config/bootstrap.go` exposes broad mutable globals (`BasePath`, `Architecture`, `DockerDir`, `DebugMode`, `Ready`, `isEMMCMachine`) that effectively become ambient process state instead of explicit, injected configuration ownership."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split config into a pure config store/loader component and a separate orchestration/service component (with explicit lifecycle start/stop) so channel handling is not coupled to config initialization; replace ambient globals with an injected ConfigService/context object consumed by callers.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "config_singleton_owner_boundary"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "config_context_laminate",
      "summary": "Runtime context abstraction is introduced but not authoritative, so package boundaries stay unclear.",
      "related_files": ["goseg/config/config.go", "goseg/config/bootstrap.go", "goseg/startram/backup_restore_runtime.go"],
      "evidence": [
        "`RuntimeContextSnapshot()` in `goseg/config/config.go` returns package-level mutable fields instead of an owned immutable context object.",
        "The same snapshot fields are mutated via `initializePaths()` in `bootstrap.go`, and `defaultRestoreBackupRuntime` in startram consumes globals indirectly through `defaultConfigService` closures (`BasePath()`/`StartramSettingsSnapshot()`), indicating mixed ownership of runtime context resolution."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace global config access with explicit context injection through function parameters or constructors, and make `RuntimeContext`/snapshot the single producer of immutable runtime values used by orchestration and service layers.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "config_singleton_owner_boundary"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "orchestration_container_dispatch_fragmentation",
      "summary": "Container type orchestration is fragmented across multiple files with duplicated mapping work, weakening predictable extension boundaries.",
      "related_files": ["goseg/docker/orchestration/container_config.go", "goseg/docker/orchestration/container_bridge.go"],
      "evidence": [
        "`ContainerConfigForTypeWithRuntime` dispatches on raw container type strings (`\"vere\"`, `\"netdata\"`, `\"minio\"`, etc.), which couples external callers to magic literals.",
        "For each container type, `container_bridge.go` manually reassembles runtime dependencies via field-by-field wiring, so adding or evolving a type impacts multiple constructors and runtime adapters instead of one extensible registry."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a cohesive orchestration registry keyed by typed container enums/contracts (factory pattern), with per-container builder structs/functions in one module so new container types require a single coherent addition and avoid duplicated wiring edits.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "orchestration_runtime_assembly"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "config package uses ambient mutable singletons as the default communication contract",
      "orchestration container type support is distributed as switch+parallel adapters instead of explicit registration"
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "config_singleton_owner_boundary",
      "orchestration_runtime_assembly"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "backup_service restore indirection in `goseg/startram/backup_service.go` and `goseg/startram/backup_restore_runtime.go` may be intentional layering for future swap-in strategies rather than a defect"
    ]
  }
}


